Note:
This file handles diagnostic reporting and LSP diagnostic integration.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process diagnostic reporting and LSP diagnostic integration
- Handle diagnostic generation and diagnostic formatting
- Manage diagnostic tracking and diagnostic metadata
- Process diagnostic communication and diagnostic protocol implementation

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Diagnostic reporting enables LSP diagnostic integration and diagnostic support
- Proper diagnostic handling ensures correct diagnostic generation and display
- Diagnostic support enables Runa compilation for LSP-integrated diagnostic handling

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Diagnostic creation with severity, location, and message
- Diagnostic engine lifecycle management (create, clear, publish)
- LSP-compatible diagnostic formatting (textDocument/publishDiagnostics)
- Diagnostic message formatting with contextual information
- Integration with the Runa compiler error pipeline

Dependencies:
- Imports compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa for owned-heap allocate/deallocate and raw memory access
- Imports compiler/internal/string_utils.runa for string operations
- Imports compiler/internal/collections.runa for diagnostic list management
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as MemoryLayout
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils
Import "compiler/internal/collections.runa" as Collections

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Diagnostic Data Structures
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Diagnostic structure (48 bytes total, 6 fields x 8 bytes each, last two packed)
Note: Layout:
Note:   offset 0:  severity (8 bytes) - SEVERITY_ERROR, WARNING, INFO, or HINT
Note:   offset 8:  start_line (8 bytes) - Zero-based line number of diagnostic start
Note:   offset 16: start_col (8 bytes) - Zero-based column of diagnostic start
Note:   offset 24: end_line (8 bytes) - Zero-based line number of diagnostic end
Note:   offset 32: end_col (8 bytes) - Zero-based column of diagnostic end
Note:   offset 40: message (8 bytes) - Pointer to diagnostic message string

Note: Extended Diagnostic with additional metadata at separate offsets
Note:   The source and code fields follow the primary 48-byte structure if needed
Note:   offset 48: source (8 bytes) - Pointer to source identifier string (e.g., "runa")
Note:   offset 56: code (8 bytes) - Diagnostic code (e.g., error number)

Type called "Diagnostic":
    severity as Integer
    start_line as Integer
    start_col as Integer
    end_line as Integer
    end_col as Integer
    message as Integer
End Type

Note: DiagnosticEngine structure (32 bytes)
Note: Layout:
Note:   offset 0:  diagnostics_list (8 bytes) - Pointer to ArrayList of Diagnostic pointers
Note:   offset 8:  diagnostic_count (8 bytes) - Number of diagnostics currently stored
Note:   offset 16: max_diagnostics (8 bytes) - Maximum diagnostics before oldest are evicted
Note:   offset 24: uri (8 bytes) - Pointer to document URI these diagnostics apply to

Type called "DiagnosticEngine":
    diagnostics_list as Integer
    diagnostic_count as Integer
    max_diagnostics as Integer
    uri as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Severity Constants (matching LSP DiagnosticSeverity values)
Note: ============================================================================

Constant SEVERITY_ERROR as Integer is 1
Constant SEVERITY_WARNING as Integer is 2
Constant SEVERITY_INFO as Integer is 3
Constant SEVERITY_HINT as Integer is 4

Note: Maximum diagnostics per document before eviction
Constant MAX_DIAGNOSTICS_PER_FILE as Integer is 500

Note: Diagnostic source identifier
Note: Pointer to "runa" string will be set at engine creation time
Constant DIAGNOSTIC_SOURCE_LENGTH as Integer is 4

Note: Return codes
Constant DIAGNOSTIC_SUCCESS as Integer is 0
Constant DIAGNOSTIC_FAILED as Integer is -1

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Diagnostic Engine Lifecycle
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "create_diagnostic_engine" takes uri as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a new diagnostic engine for a specific document URI
    Note: Allocates the DiagnosticEngine structure and internal diagnostics list
    Note: The engine stores diagnostics as they are generated by the compiler
    Note: and formats them for the LSP client on demand
    
    Note: Parameters:
    Note:   uri - Pointer to document URI string this engine reports diagnostics for
    
    Note: Returns pointer to DiagnosticEngine, or 0 on allocation failure

    Note: Allocate DiagnosticEngine structure (32 bytes)
    Let engine be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 32
    If engine is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate the diagnostics array (MAX_DIAGNOSTICS_PER_FILE pointers)
    Let diag_array be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with MAX_DIAGNOSTICS_PER_FILE multiplied by 8
    If diag_array is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from MemoryLayout with engine
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Zero out the diagnostics array
    Let zero_idx be 0
    While zero_idx is less than MAX_DIAGNOSTICS_PER_FILE:
        Let dummy_z be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_array, zero_idx multiplied by 8, 0
        Set zero_idx to zero_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Initialize engine fields
    Let dummy_list be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 0, diag_array
    Let dummy_count be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 8, 0
    Let dummy_max be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 16, MAX_DIAGNOSTICS_PER_FILE
    Let dummy_uri be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 24, uri

    Return engine
End Process

Process called "add_diagnostic" takes engine as Integer, diagnostic as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add a diagnostic to the engine's collection
    Note: If the diagnostic count has reached max_diagnostics, the oldest diagnostic
    Note: is evicted (freed) and replaced by the new one (circular buffer behavior)
    
    Note: Parameters:
    Note:   engine - Pointer to DiagnosticEngine
    Note:   diagnostic - Pointer to Diagnostic structure to add
    
    Note: Returns DIAGNOSTIC_SUCCESS on success, DIAGNOSTIC_FAILED on error

    If engine is equal to 0:
        Return DIAGNOSTIC_FAILED
    End If
    If diagnostic is equal to 0:
        Return DIAGNOSTIC_FAILED
    End If

    Let diag_list be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 0
    If diag_list is equal to 0:
        Return DIAGNOSTIC_FAILED
    End If

    Let current_count be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 8
    Let max_count be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 16

    If current_count is less than max_count:
        Note: Space available - add at the end
        Let dummy_add be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_list, current_count multiplied by 8, diagnostic
        Let dummy_inc be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 8, current_count plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Note: List is full - evict oldest (index 0) and shift everything down
        Note: Free the oldest diagnostic
        Let oldest be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_list, 0
        If oldest is not equal to 0:
            Note: Free the message string of the evicted diagnostic
            Let old_msg be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with oldest, 40
            If old_msg is not equal to 0:
                Let dummy_free_msg be proc deallocate from MemoryLayout with old_msg
            End If
            Let dummy_free_old be proc deallocate from MemoryLayout with oldest
        End If

        Note: Shift all diagnostics down by one position
        Let shift_idx be 0
        While shift_idx is less than max_count minus 1:
            Let next_diag be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_list, shift_idx plus 1 multiplied by 8
            Let dummy_shift be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_list, shift_idx multiplied by 8, next_diag
            Set shift_idx to shift_idx plus 1
        End While

        Note: Add new diagnostic at the last position
        Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_list, max_count minus 1 multiplied by 8, diagnostic
    End If

    Return DIAGNOSTIC_SUCCESS
End Process

Process called "clear_diagnostics" takes engine as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Clear all diagnostics from the engine
    Note: Frees each diagnostic and its message string, then resets the count to 0
    
    Note: Returns DIAGNOSTIC_SUCCESS on success, DIAGNOSTIC_FAILED on error

    If engine is equal to 0:
        Return DIAGNOSTIC_FAILED
    End If

    Let diag_list be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 0
    If diag_list is equal to 0:
        Return DIAGNOSTIC_FAILED
    End If

    Let current_count be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 8

    Note: Free each diagnostic and its message
    Let free_idx be 0
    While free_idx is less than current_count:
        Let diag_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_list, free_idx multiplied by 8
        If diag_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Note: Free the message string
            Let msg_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_ptr, 40
            If msg_ptr is not equal to 0:
                Let dummy_free_msg be proc deallocate from MemoryLayout with msg_ptr
            End If
            Note: Free the diagnostic structure itself
            Let dummy_free_diag be proc deallocate from MemoryLayout with diag_ptr
            Let dummy_clear_slot be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_list, free_idx multiplied by 8, 0
        End If
        Set free_idx to free_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Reset count to 0
    Let dummy_reset be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 8, 0

    Return DIAGNOSTIC_SUCCESS
End Process

Process called "publish_diagnostics" takes engine as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Build a textDocument/publishDiagnostics notification JSON payload
    Note: Formats all current diagnostics into LSP-compatible JSON
    
    Note: The JSON structure follows the LSP specification:
    Note: {
    Note:   "uri": "<document_uri>",
    Note:   "diagnostics": [
    Note:     {
    Note:       "range": {"start":{"line":<l>,"character":<c>},"end":{"line":<l>,"character":<c>}},
    Note:       "severity": <severity>,
    Note:       "source": "runa",
    Note:       "message": "<message>"
    Note:     },
    Note:     ...
    Note:   ]
    Note: }
    
    Note: Returns pointer to JSON string buffer, or 0 on failure

    If engine is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let diag_list be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 0
    Let diag_count be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 8
    Let uri_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with engine, 24

    Note: Allocate a buffer for the JSON output (estimate 256 bytes per diagnostic + overhead)
    Let buf_size be diag_count multiplied by 256 plus 512
    If buf_size is less than 1024:
        Set buf_size to 1024
    End If
    Let json_buf be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with buf_size
    If json_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let pos be 0

    Note: {"uri":"
    Let dummy_ob be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 123
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_q1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 34
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Note: u=117, r=114, i=105
    Let dummy_u be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 117
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_r be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 114
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_i be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 105
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_q2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 34
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_colon1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 58
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_q3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 34
    Set pos to pos plus 1

    Note: Copy URI string
    If uri_ptr is not equal to 0:
        Let uri_len be proc measure_string_len with uri_ptr
        Let ui be 0
        While ui is less than uri_len:
            Let ub be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with uri_ptr, ui
            Let dummy_ub be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, ub
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set ui to ui plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: ","diagnostics":[
    Let dummy_q4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 34
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_comma be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 44
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_q5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 34
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Note: d=100, i=105, a=97, g=103, n=110, o=111, s=115, t=116, i=105, c=99, s=115
    Let diag_key_bytes be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 16
    If diag_key_bytes is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_d1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 100
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_i1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 105
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_a1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 97
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_g1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 103
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_n1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 110
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_o1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 111
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_s1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 115
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_t1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 116
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_i2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 105
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_c1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 99
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_s2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 115
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_free_dk be proc deallocate from MemoryLayout with diag_key_bytes
    End If
    Let dummy_q6 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 34
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_colon2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 58
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Note: Opening bracket for array
    Let dummy_bracket be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 91
    Set pos to pos plus 1

    Note: Format each diagnostic as a JSON object
    Let diag_idx be 0
    While diag_idx is less than diag_count:
        If diag_idx is greater than 0:
            Let dummy_sep be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 44
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        End If

        Let diag_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_list, diag_idx multiplied by 8
        If diag_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let formatted_len be proc format_single_diagnostic with json_buf, pos, diag_ptr
            Set pos to pos plus formatted_len
        End If

        Set diag_idx to diag_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Close diagnostics array and root object: ]}
    Let dummy_close_arr be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 93
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_close_obj be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 125
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with json_buf, pos, 0

    Return json_buf
End Process

Process called "create_diagnostic" takes severity as Integer, start_line as Integer, start_col as Integer, end_line as Integer, end_col as Integer, message as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a new Diagnostic structure with the given properties
    Note: Allocates a 48-byte Diagnostic on the owned heap
    
    Note: Parameters:
    Note:   severity - SEVERITY_ERROR, SEVERITY_WARNING, SEVERITY_INFO, or SEVERITY_HINT
    Note:   start_line - Zero-based start line
    Note:   start_col - Zero-based start column
    Note:   end_line - Zero-based end line
    Note:   end_col - Zero-based end column
    Note:   message - Pointer to diagnostic message string (ownership transferred)
    
    Note: Returns pointer to Diagnostic, or 0 on allocation failure

    Let diag be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 48
    If diag is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dummy_sev be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with diag, 0, severity
    Let dummy_sl be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with diag, 8, start_line
    Let dummy_sc be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with diag, 16, start_col
    Let dummy_el be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with diag, 24, end_line
    Let dummy_ec be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with diag, 32, end_col
    Let dummy_msg be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with diag, 40, message

    Return diag
End Process

Process called "format_diagnostic_message" takes severity as Integer, line as Integer, col as Integer, message as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Format a diagnostic message into a human-readable string
    Note: Format: "<severity>: <message> (line <line>, col <col>)"
    Note: Returns pointer to newly allocated formatted string, or 0 on failure

    If message is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Calculate required buffer size
    Note: Severity label (max 7 chars "warning") + ": " (2) + message + " (line " (7) + digits + ", col " (6) + digits + ")" (1) + null
    Let msg_len be proc measure_string_len with message
    Let buf_size be msg_len plus 64
    Let result_buf be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with buf_size
    If result_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let pos be 0

    Note: Write severity label
    If severity is equal to SEVERITY_ERROR:
        Note: "error" e=101, r=114, r=114, o=111, r=114
        Let dummy_e be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 101
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_r1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 114
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_r2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 114
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_o be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 111
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_r3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 114
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    Otherwise If severity is equal to SEVERITY_WARNING:
        Note: "warning" w=119, a=97, r=114, n=110, i=105, n=110, g=103
        Let dummy_w be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 119
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_a be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 97
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_r be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 114
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_n be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 110
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_i be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 105
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_n2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 110
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_g be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 103
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    Otherwise If severity is equal to SEVERITY_INFO:
        Note: "info" i=105, n=110, f=102, o=111
        Set dummy_i to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 105
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Set dummy_n to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 110
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_f be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 102
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Set dummy_o to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 111
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Note: "hint" h=104, i=105, n=110, t=116
        Let dummy_h be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 104
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Set dummy_i to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 105
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Set dummy_n to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 110
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let dummy_t be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 116
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If

    Note: Write ": "
    Let dummy_colon be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 58
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_space be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 32
    Set pos to pos plus 1

    Note: Copy message
    Let mi be 0
    While mi is less than msg_len:
        Let mb be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with message, mi
        Let dummy_mb be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, mb
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Set mi to mi plus 1
    End While

    Note: Write " (line "
    Let dummy_sp2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 32
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_lp be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 40
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Note: l=108, i=105, n=110, e=101
    Let dummy_l be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 108
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_i2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 105
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Set dummy_n2 to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 110
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Set dummy_e to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 101
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_sp3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 32
    Set pos to pos plus 1

    Note: Write line number (1-based for display)
    Let display_line be line plus 1
    Let line_digits be proc write_digits_to_buffer with result_buf, pos, display_line
    Set pos to pos plus line_digits

    Note: Write ", col "
    Let dummy_comma be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 44
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_sp4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 32
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Note: c=99, o=111, l=108
    Let dummy_c be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 99
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_o2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 111
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_l2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 108
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_sp5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 32
    Set pos to pos plus 1

    Note: Write column number (1-based for display)
    Let display_col be col plus 1
    Let col_digits be proc write_digits_to_buffer with result_buf, pos, display_col
    Set pos to pos plus col_digits

    Note: Write closing paren and null terminator
    Let dummy_rp be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 41
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let dummy_null be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result_buf, pos, 0

    Return result_buf
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal Helper Processes
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "format_single_diagnostic" takes buf as Integer, pos as Integer, diag_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Format a single diagnostic into JSON at the given buffer position
    Note: JSON format: {"range":{"start":{"line":<l>,"character":<c>},"end":{"line":<l>,"character":<c>}},"severity":<s>,"source":"runa","message":"<msg>"}
    Note: Returns number of bytes written

    If diag_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let severity be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_ptr, 0
    Let start_line be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_ptr, 8
    Let start_col be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_ptr, 16
    Let end_line be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_ptr, 24
    Let end_col be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_ptr, 32
    Let msg_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with diag_ptr, 40

    Let p be pos

    Note: Opening brace
    Let dummy_ob be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 123
    Set p to p plus 1

    Note: "range":{"start":{"line":
    Let dummy_q1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 34
    Set p to p plus 1
    Note: r=114, a=97, n=110, g=103, e=101
    Let dummy_r1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 114
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_a1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 97
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_n1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 110
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_g1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 103
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_e1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 101
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_q2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 34
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_colon1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 58
    Set p to p plus 1
    Note: {"start":{"line":
    Let dummy_ob2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 123
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_q3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 34
    Set p to p plus 1
    Note: s=115, t=116, a=97, r=114, t=116
    Let dummy_s1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 115
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_t1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 116
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_a2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 97
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_r2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 114
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_t2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 116
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_q4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 34
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_colon2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 58
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_ob3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 123
    Set p to p plus 1
    Note: "line":
    Let dummy_q5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 34
    Set p to p plus 1
    Let dummy_l1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with buf, p, 108
    Set p to p plus 1
